<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>89878</id>
    <title>After using the Scaling function the Options dialog size is no longer adaptable (+ inconsistent behaviour)</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">I recognized this (these) bug(s) while investigating bug 89874.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">If you are using the Scaling function to enlarge the menus and then changing it back to 100% the OPTIONS dialog size is no longer adaptable.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">Furthermore, the size of the OPTIONS dialog does not automatically adapt to the increased size of the text in the dialog.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">1 Open WRITER</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.3">2 Go to TOOLS -&gt; OPTIONS -&gt; section LIBREOFFICE -&gt; subsection VIEW and select Scaling to e.g. 150% and press OK</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Interim Result: The font size of the menu and the formatting toolbar items is increased.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">3 Go to TOOLS -&gt; OPTIONS -&gt; section LIBREOFFICE -&gt; subsection VIEW</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">Interim Result: It is impossible to read all the entries in the OPTIONS dialog (see section "User Interface" and "Mouse").</sentence>
            <sentence id="6.2">-&gt; Enhancement: It would be good if the dialog would automatically adapt its size, if possible.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="7">
            <sentence id="7.1">4 Now extend the size (width) of the OPTIONS dialog, that you can read the whole dialog and press OK</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.2">5 Go to TOOLS -&gt; OPTIONS -&gt; section LIBREOFFICE -&gt; subsection VIEW</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="8">
            <sentence id="8.1">Interim Result: The OPTIONS dialog is again too small, though you have increased it in step 4.</sentence>
            <sentence id="8.2">Bug: It would be good if the dialog would keep its size.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="9">
            <sentence id="9.1">6 Now extend again the size (width) of the OPTIONS dialog, that you can read the whole dialog and change the Scaling back to 100% and press OK</sentence>
            <sentence id="9.2">7 Go to TOOLS -&gt; OPTIONS -&gt; section LIBREOFFICE -&gt; subsection VIEW</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="10">
            <sentence id="10.1">Interim Result: The dialog is still increased, which seems to be inconsistent with the bug in step 5.</sentence>
            <sentence id="10.2">Bug: The dialog should have again the original size of step 2.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="11">
            <sentence id="11.1">8 Now try to reduce the size of the dialog.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="12">
            <sentence id="12.1">Result: It is impossible to reduce the size of the dialog.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="13">
            <sentence id="13.1">9 Close and reopen LO and then everything is fine again</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="14">
            <sentence id="14.1">Reproducible with LO 4.4.1.2, Win 8.1</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
